    <section id="id1164934208179">
      <title>[LO 3.8]</title>
      <para id="id1164936527597">HOMEWORK ASSIGNMENT</para>
      <para id="id1164927289921">Bring a collection of 10 different textures to school by means of <emphasis effect="bold">frottage</emphasis>. Frottage is a technique through which an image is attained by placing a sheet of paper over a textured object and using a soft pencil (2B, 4B or 6B) for rubbing across the surface of the paper. A familiar example is obtained by placing a coin under a piece of paper and rubbing over the paper with a pencil.</para>
      <para id="id1164927492704"><emphasis effect="bold">Think of getting textures from examples</emphasis> such as: shoe soles, brick walls, wooden floors, different materials, etc.</para>
